OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F369A1781617682
OL,3,CManchester IRA bombing: What happened
OL,4,Cand how the city was rebuilt
OL,6,FThirty years ago, on the 15 June 1996,
OL,7,Ftwo IRA members planted a bomb on
OL,8,FCorporation Street, outside
OL,9,FManchester's Arndale shopping centre.
OL,10,FIt would be the biggest bomb on UK
OL,11,Fmainland since the second world war.
OL,13,FRemarkably, no one died, but 200
OL,14,Fpeople were injured and the bomb
OL,15,Fripped out the heart of the city's
OL,16,Fretail sector, changing the face of
OL,17,FManchester forever.
OL,19,FWhat happened?
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G1/10
OL,2,W/*%+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
