OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F369A1781617682
OL,3,CManchester IRA bombing: What happened
OL,4,Cand how the city was rebuilt
OL,6,FThe attack came on a sunny Saturday
OL,7,Fbefore Fathers Day, as the Arndale was
OL,8,Fpacked with shoppers. Football fans
OL,9,Fwere also in town for the next day's
OL,10,FRussia v Germany fixture at nearby Old
OL,11,FTrafford.
OL,13,FAt 9.20am two men drove a white Ford
OL,14,Fcargo van into Manchester city centre.
OL,15,FThey parked on double yellow lines on
OL,16,FCorporation Street, next to Marks &
OL,17,FSpencer, and then walked away.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G2/10
OL,2,W/*%+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,370,360,120,260,000,100
PN,36903
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F369A1781617682
OL,3,CManchester IRA bombing: What happened
OL,4,Cand how the city was rebuilt
OL,6,F23 minutes later, Gary Hall, a
OL,7,Fsecurity guard at ITV's Granada
OL,8,Fstudios, received a phone call from a
OL,9,Fman with a "very calm" Irish voice. He
OL,10,Fsaid he had planted a bomb that would
OL,11,Fexplode an hour later.
OL,13,FPolice immediately began evacuating
OL,14,Fabout 80,000 people from the city
OL,15,Fcentre, while attempts were made to
OL,16,Ffind the bomb.
OL,18,FAmid the panic, a police officer
OL,19,Fspotted the white vehicle and noticed
OL,20,Fwires running from the dashboard.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G3/10
OL,2,W/*%+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,370,360,120,260,000,100
PN,36904
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F369A1781617682
OL,3,CManchester IRA bombing: What happened
OL,4,Cand how the city was rebuilt
OL,6,FBomb disposal officers attempted to
OL,7,Fdefuse the explosive with a remote-
OL,8,Fcontrolled robot but the attempt
OL,9,Ffailed and, at 11.17am, the 3,300lb
OL,10,Fdevice exploded.
OL,12,FSmoke mushroomed high above the city
OL,13,Fwhile buildings shook and glass
OL,14,Fshattered, raining debris on people
OL,15,Foutside the cordoned area.
OL,17,FNo one was killed, but the blast
OL,18,Fcaused extensive damage. 200 people
OL,19,Fwere injured and many more were left
OL,20,Ftraumatised by the attack.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G4/10
OL,2,W/*%+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,370,360,120,260,000,100
PN,36905
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F369A1781617682
OL,3,CManchester IRA bombing: What happened
OL,4,Cand how the city was rebuilt
OL,6,FLee Cullen was a Tactical Aid Unit
OL,7,Fconstable for Greater Manchester
OL,8,FPolice (GMP) on the day of the attack,
OL,9,Fhe recalls the scale of the bomb as it
OL,10,Fwent off.
OL,12,F"When the bomb went off, I was in
OL,13,Fdirect eyesight of the device as it
OL,14,Fdetonated," he said.
OL,16,F"The bright flash followed
OL,17,Finstantaneously by a huge fire ball
OL,18,Fand percussion wave is something that
OL,19,Fhas lived with me to this day. I had
OL,20,Fheard explosions before but that
OL,21,Fsound, a huge deep crump was deafening.
OL,26,@xD@AOU
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G5/10
OL,2,W/*%+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,370,360,120,260,000,100
PN,36906
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F369A1781617682
OL,3,CManchester IRA bombing: What happened
OL,4,Cand how the city was rebuilt
OL,6,F"The amount of debris that was thrown
OL,7,Fout from the epicentre was
OL,8,Fsubstantial. People were showered in
OL,9,Fglass at my location and some people
OL,10,Fsuffered lacerations from falling
OL,11,Fglass as buildings bowed under the
OL,12,Fblast."
OL,14,FDamage and restoration
OL,16,FEntire sections of the city centre
OL,17,Fwere devastated, estimates put the
OL,18,Fcost at around #700 million, making it
OL,19,Fone of the most expensive terrorist
OL,20,Fattacks in British history at the time.
OL,26,@nD@AOU
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G6/10
OL,2,W/*%+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,370,360,120,260,000,100
PN,36907
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F369A1781617682
OL,3,CManchester IRA bombing: What happened
OL,4,Cand how the city was rebuilt
OL,6,FThe blast destroyed the Marks &
OL,7,FSpencer store and Longridge House. The
OL,8,FArndale Centre itself sustained severe
OL,9,Fstructural damage making a no go area
OL,10,Ffor months and put a third of the
OL,11,Fcity's retail space out of use.
OL,13,FDespite much of Corporation Street
OL,14,Fcrumbling, one thing stood proud a red
OL,15,Fpost box, which would become a symbol
OL,16,Fof resilience in the city.
OL,18,FPlans to regenerate Manchester were
OL,19,Falready in place before the bombing.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G7/10
OL,2,W/*%+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,370,360,120,260,000,100
PN,36908
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F369A1781617682
OL,3,CManchester IRA bombing: What happened
OL,4,Cand how the city was rebuilt
OL,6,FA tram network had been reintroduced,
OL,7,FCastlefield and Ancoats had major
OL,8,Fredevelopment strategies in place, and
OL,9,Fthe city was preparing to host the
OL,10,F2002 Commonwealth Games.
OL,12,FHowever parts of city, including
OL,13,FDeansgate and Victoria, were being
OL,14,Fleft behind. The bomb presented city
OL,15,Fplanners with a unique opportunity to
OL,16,Frebuild the city in a new way and fast
OL,17,Ftrack further development.
OL,19,FManchester rose from the ashes with
OL,20,Fnew boulevards and parks, traffic-free
OL,21,Fsquares and bus-only streets.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G8/10
OL,2,W/*%+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,370,360,120,260,000,100
PN,36909
SC,0009
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F369A1781617682
OL,3,CManchester IRA bombing: What happened
OL,4,Cand how the city was rebuilt
OL,6,FMarks and Spencer opened it new home
OL,7,Fin 1999 and a shiny new Cathedral
OL,8,FStreet attracted big name luxury
OL,9,Fstores such as Selfridiges and Harvey
OL,10,FNichols.
OL,12,FThe investigation to date
OL,14,FTo this day, nobody from the IRA has
OL,15,Fbeen convicted of plotting, assisting
OL,16,For carrying out the bombing.
OL,18,FOn the 11 June, a decision was made by
OL,19,FCounter Terrorism Police to close the
OL,20,Finvestigation into the attack.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G9/10
OL,2,W/*%+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,370,360,120,260,000,100
PN,36910
SC,0010
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F369A1781617682
OL,3,CManchester IRA bombing: What happened
OL,4,Cand how the city was rebuilt
OL,6,FDespite a review being launched a
OL,7,Fdecade ago to see if new techniques or
OL,8,Finformation could aid the
OL,9,Finvestigation, detectives now say all
OL,10,Flines of enquiry have been exhausted.
OL,12,FA man was arrested at Birmingham
OL,13,Fairport in September 2022, and
OL,14,Freleased without charge after
OL,15,Finterview.
OL,17,FPolice say another man would have been
OL,18,Farrested and interviewed, but he died
OL,19,Fseveral years ago, before an arrest
OL,20,Fcould take place.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}     G10/10
OL,2,W/*%+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
